content:
Schedule a daily app refresh to update the dataflow before you start exploring event data with Event Monitoring Analytics.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Requires Salesforce Shield or Salesforce Event Monitoring add-on subscriptions.

To create and manage Event Monitoring Analytics Apps: Access Event Monitoring Analytics Templates and Apps, Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps, Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows.

When you create Event Monitoring Analytics, a dataflow runs one time to import the latest Event Monitoring data to CRM Analytics. To ensure that your app uses up-to-date Salesforce data, you can schedule the app to refresh your data every day.

Salesforce uploads event log files after they’re generated. Most dataset uploads finish at about the same time each day. Exact finish times vary depending on dataset size and content.

To get the most out of your scheduled data refresh, follow these best practices: Schedule the app refresh a few hours after event log files are generated. Add the new "Add only new event log file data to existing datasets?" app configuration to prevent overwriting full datasets every day.

To add this setting to your app, see Create an Event Monitoring Analytics App That Incrementally Refreshes Data.

Multiple background Salesforce processes trigger event log file uploads. To schedule your app, see Schedule Data Refresh for a CRM Analytics App. Select a time outside normal work hours so the data refresh doesn’t interrupt business activities.

Note: The append dataflow deletes all data in the dataset that supplies your app with new data, regardless of the specified retention period.
title: Schedule Daily Data Refresh for Event Monitoring Analytics
